The paper discusses the design of indexes for spatial and temporal data, which is a common topic in the database (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The focus on space filling curves (SFCs) and clustering performance suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's emphasis on efficiency and optimization suggests that it may also be relevant to the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
